<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 717/96 of 19 April 1996 adopting exceptional support measures for the beef and veal market in Belgium, France and the Netherlands </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) NR 717/96, millega v&otilde;etakse vastu Belgia, Prantsusmaa ja Madalmaade veise- ja vasikalihaturu toetamise erandmeetmed </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> 19. aprill 1996 EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 805/68 of 27 June 1968 on the common organization of the market in beef and veal (1), as last amended by Commission Regulation (EC) No 2417/95 (2), and in particular Article 23 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 27. juuni 1968. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 805/68 veise- ja vasikalihaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, viimati muudetud komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2417/95, eriti selle artiklit 23, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Decision 96/239/EEC of 27 March 1996 on emergency measures to protect against bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE) (3) prohibits the exportation of live bovine animals, or any part of them, from the United Kingdom to other Member States and their export to third countries as a result of the incidence of BSE in the United Kingdom; whereas calves born in the United Kingdom had been exported to other Member States for fattening prior to the introduction of that export ban; whereas the possibility that these calves may enter the human food or animal feed chains has led to a lack of consumer confidence in beef and a disturbance of the markets in Belgium, France and the Netherlands; whereas it is therefore necessary to take exceptional measures to support these markets; whereas it is appropriate to establish a Community co-financed scheme authorizing Belgium, France and the Netherlands to purchase the animals concerned with a view to killing and subsequently destroying them; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: komisjoni 27. m&auml;rtsi 1996. aasta otsusega 96/239/E&Uuml; erakorralistest kaitsemeetmetest veiste spongiaalse entsefalopaatia (BSE-t&otilde;ve) vastu keelatakse BSE-t&otilde;ve juhtude t&otilde;ttu &Uuml;hendkuningriigis elusveiste v&otilde;i veiseosade toimetamine &Uuml;hendkuningriigist teistesse liikmesriikidesse ja nende eksport kolmandatesse riikidesse; enne nimetatud ekspordikeelu kehtestamist oli &Uuml;hendkuningriigis s&uuml;ndinud vasikaid eksporditud nuumamiseks teistesse liikmesriikidesse; v&otilde;imalus, et k&otilde;nealused vasikad satuvad inimeste v&otilde;i loomade toiduahelasse, on p&otilde;hjustanud tarbija usalduse kadumise veiseliha suhtes ja h&auml;irinud turgu Belgias, Prantsusmaal ja Madalmaades; seet&otilde;ttu on vaja v&otilde;tta nende turgude toetamiseks erandmeetmeid; on asjakohane luua &uuml;henduse kaasrahastamisel kava, mis lubaks Belgial, Prantsusmaal ja Madalmaadel osta k&otilde;nealuseid loomi eesm&auml;rgiga need tappa ja seej&auml;rel h&auml;vitada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in view of the extent of the disease and consequently of the magnitude of the efforts needed to support the market, it would be appropriate for such efforts to be shared by the Community and the Member States concerned; </inglise>
<eesti> haiguse levikut ja turu toetamiseks vajalike j&otilde;upingutuste sellele vastavat suurusj&auml;rku silmas pidades oleks kohane, kui &uuml;hendus ja asjaomased liikmesriigid neid j&otilde;upingutusi jagaksid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the most recently observed price of carcases of calves on the Community market was equivalent to ECU 2,8 per kilogram live weight and that it is therefore appropriate to base the purchase price on this, without prejudice to the possibility of subsequent adjustment in the light of developments; whereas, in similar cases the Community has contributed to the overall expenditure incurred at a rate of 70 %; whereas it is appropriate, to provide a Community contribution of 70 % of the purchase price paid by Belgium, France and by the Netherlands per animal destroyed under this Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> viimati &uuml;henduse turul t&auml;heldatud vasikar&uuml;mpade hind v&otilde;rdus 2,8 ek&uuml;&uuml;ga eluskaalu kilogrammi kohta ja seet&otilde;ttu oleks kohane v&otilde;tta see ostuhinna aluseks, ilma et see v&auml;listaks v&otilde;imalust hiljem korrigeerida hinda vastavalt turu arengule; samasugustel juhtudel on &uuml;hendus rahastanud kulutuste &uuml;ldsummast 70%; &uuml;hendusel on kohane tasuda 70% sellest ostuhinnast, mida maksavad Belgia, Prantsusmaa ja Madalmaad iga k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt h&auml;vitatud looma kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, it is necessary to ensure that the animals concerned are killed and destroyed in a hygienic manner; whereas the price paid to producers is to compensate them for not selling the calves in question; whereas those calves must therefore be prohibited from being marketed; whereas it is therefore necessary to specify the conditions for the destruction of these animals and of the controls to be carried out by the authorities of the Member States concerned; </inglise>
<eesti> on vaja tagada, et k&otilde;nealused loomad tapetaks ja h&auml;vitataks h&uuml;gieeniliselt; tootjatele makstav hind on m&otilde;eldud neile kompensatsiooniks k&otilde;nealuste vasikate m&uuml;&uuml;mata j&auml;tmise eest; nende vasikate turustamine tuleb seet&otilde;ttu keelustada; sellep&auml;rast on vajalik t&auml;psustada nende loomade h&auml;vitamise ja k&otilde;nealuste liikmesriikide asutuste poolt korraldatava kontrolli tingimusi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, provision should be made for Commission experts to check compliance with the conditions as specified; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleks s&auml;testada komisjoni ekspertide v&otilde;imalus kontrollida t&auml;psustatud tingimuste t&auml;itmist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Beef and Veal, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las veise- ja vasikalihaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authorities in Belgium, France and the Netherlands shall be authorized to purchase any bovine animal aged six months or less on 20 March 1996 and present on that date on a holding located in the territory of Belgium, France or the Netherlands respectively presented to them by any producer, which can be proved by him to have been born in the United Kingdom. </inglise>
<eesti> Belgia, Prantsusmaa ja Madalmaade p&auml;devatele asutustele antakse luba osta 20. m&auml;rtsil 1996 mis tahes kuue kuu vanust v&otilde;i nooremat veist, keda peetakse sel ajal Belgia, Prantsusmaa v&otilde;i Madalmaade territooriumil asuvas p&otilde;llumajandusettev&otilde;ttes ja kelle suhtes tootja suudab t&otilde;estada, et ta on s&uuml;ndinud &Uuml;hendkuningriigi territooriumil. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The animals referred to in paragraph 1 shall be killed in specially designated slaughterhouses. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud loomad tapetakse spetsiaalselt selleks etten&auml;htud tapamajades. </eesti>
<inglise> If the hide is removed the head, internal organs and carcases shall be permanently stained. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui nahk on eemaldatud, m&auml;rgistatakse pea, siseorganid ja r&uuml;mp kustumatu v&auml;rviga. </eesti>
<inglise> The stained material or the whole animal shall be transported in sealed containers to specially authorized incineration or rendering plants for disposal in such a way that no part of it may be placed on the market. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;rgistatud materjal v&otilde;i kogu loom transporditakse pitseeritud konteineris eriloa saanud tuhastamis- v&otilde;i j&auml;&auml;tmetehastesse h&auml;vitamiseks niisugusel viisil, et selle &uuml;htki osa ei saaks turule viia. </eesti>
<inglise> No part of the abovementioned animals may enter into the human food or animal feed chains or be used for cosmetic or pharmaceutical products. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;kski eespool osutatud loomade osa ei tohi sattuda inimeste v&otilde;i loomade toiduahelasse, samuti ei tohi neid kasutada kosmeetika- v&otilde;i farmaatsiatoodetes. </eesti>
<inglise> A representative of the competent authority of Belgium, France and the Netherlands respectively shall be permanently present in the slaughterhouses referred to above in order to supervise the operations in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Belgia, Prantsusmaa ja Madalmaade p&auml;devate asutuste esindajad on eespool nimetatud tapamajades p&uuml;sivalt kohal, et teostada k&otilde;nealuste toimingute j&auml;relevalvet. </eesti>
<inglise> Notwithstanding the first subparagraph, the competent authorities of Belgium, France and the Netherlands may allow the on-farm slaughter of an animal where existing animal welfare practice would require this. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks esimese l&otilde;igu kohaldamist, v&otilde;ivad Belgia, Prantsusmaa ja Madalmaade p&auml;devad asutused lubada looma tapmist p&otilde;llumajandusettev&otilde;ttes, kui seda n&otilde;uab loomakaitsetava. </eesti>
<inglise> Notwithstanding the second subparagraph, the hides of the animals referred to in paragraph 1 do not have to be stained or destroyed provided that they have been treated in such a way that they can only be used for leather production. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks teise l&otilde;igu kohaldamist, ei pea m&auml;rgistama ja h&auml;vitama l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud loomade nahku tingimusel, et neid on t&ouml;&ouml;deldud viisil, mis laseb neid kasutada ainult nahatoodete valmistamisel. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The slaughterhouses referred to in paragraph 2 shall be organized and operated in such a way as to ensure that: </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud tapamaju korraldatakse ja k&auml;itatakse viisil, mis tagab, et: </eesti>
<inglise> - no bovine animal, the product from the slaughter of which is intended for human or animal consumption, is present in the slaughterhouse when animals are being slaughtered under this scheme or in the lairage of the slaughterhouse when animals to be slaughtered under this scheme are present, and </inglise>
<eesti> - &uuml;kski veis, mille tapasaadused on m&otilde;eldud inimestele v&otilde;i loomadele tarbimiseks, ei ole tapamajas ajal, kui loomi tapetakse vastavalt k&auml;esolevale kavale, v&otilde;i tapamaja ootetarandikus, kui seal on loomi, keda kavatsetakse tappa vastavalt k&auml;esolevale kavale; ja </eesti>
<inglise> - where it is necessary for products derived from animals slaughtered under the scheme to be stored, such storage shall be separate from any storage facility used for meat or other products destined for human or animal consumption. </inglise>
<eesti> - kui k&auml;esoleva kava kohaselt tapetud veiste tapasaadusi on vaja ladustada, asub k&otilde;nealune ladu eraldi k&otilde;igist sellistest hoiuruumidest, mida kasutatakse inimestele v&otilde;i loomadele tarbimiseks m&otilde;eldud liha v&otilde;i muude toodete hoidmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authority of the Member State concerned shall: </inglise>
<eesti> Asjaomase liikmesriigi p&auml;dev asutus: </eesti>
<inglise> - carry out the necessary administrative checks and effective on-the-spot supervision of the operations referred to in paragraphs 2 and 3, and </inglise>
<eesti> - korraldab vajalikke halduskontrolle ja t&otilde;husat kohapealset j&auml;relevalvet l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 osutatud toimingute &uuml;le ning </eesti>
<inglise> - control those operations on the basis of frequent and unannounced inspections, in particular to verify that all material has been effectively destroyed; </inglise>
<eesti> - kontrollib neid toiminguid sagedaste ja etteteatamata kontrollreidide alusel, eelk&otilde;ige selleks, et veenduda, kas kogu materjal on tegelikult h&auml;vitatud. </eesti>
<inglise> The results of these checks and controls shall be made available to the Commission on request. </inglise>
<eesti> Nende kontrollimiste ja &uuml;levaatuste tulemused tehakse taotluse korral k&auml;ttesaadavaks komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> If the number of animals presented for sale and subsequent destruction exceeds the number for which there is capacity to destroy in the Member State concerned, the competent authority may limit access to this scheme. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui ostmiseks ja sellele j&auml;rgnevaks h&auml;vitamiseks esitatud loomade arv &uuml;letab arvu, mille h&auml;vitamiseks asjaomasel liikmesriigil on v&otilde;imsusi, v&otilde;ib p&auml;dev asutus k&auml;esolevas kavas osalemist piirata. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The price in respect of the animal to be paid by the competent authority of the Member State concerned under Article 1 (1) shall be ECU 2,8 per kilogram live weight. </inglise>
<eesti> Looma hind, mis artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 1 kohaselt maksab k&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi p&auml;dev asutus, on 2,8 ek&uuml;&uuml;d eluskaalu kilogrammi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> If the weight is assessed after the animal has been bled, the weight shall be increased by 5 %. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kaalu hinnatakse p&auml;rast looma veretustamist, suurendatakse kaalu 5% v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Community shall co-finance the purchase price paid by the Member State concerned per purchased animal which has been destroyed in accordance with the provisions of Article 1, at a rate of 70 %. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendus kaasrahastab 70% k&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi makstud hinnast iga ostetud looma eest, kes on h&auml;vitatud artikli 1 s&auml;tete kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The conversion rate to be applied shall be the agricultural rate in force on the first day of the month of purchase of the animal in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Kohaldatav &uuml;mberarvestuskurss on p&otilde;llumajanduslik &uuml;mberarvestuskurss, mis kehtib k&otilde;nealuse looma ostukuu esimesel p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Belgium, France and the Netherlands shall adopt all measures necessary to ensure its proper application and full compliance with the provisions of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Belgia, Prantsusmaa ja Madalmaad v&otilde;tavad k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse asjakohaseks rakendamiseks ja selle s&auml;tete t&auml;ielikuks j&auml;rgimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall inform the Commission as soon as possible of the measures which they have taken and of any amendments thereto. </inglise>
<eesti> Nad teavitavad komisjoni niipea kui v&otilde;imalik v&otilde;etud meetmetest ja neisse tehtud parandustest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authorities in Belgium, France and the Netherlands: </inglise>
<eesti> Belgia, Prantsusmaa ja Madalmaade p&auml;devad asutused: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) shall inform the Commission each Wednesday, of the number of animals: - purchased, and </inglise>
<eesti> a. teatavad komisjonile igal kolmap&auml;eval loomade arvu, kes eelneva n&auml;dala jooksul on k&auml;esoleva kava kohaselt: </eesti>
<inglise> - slaughtered, </inglise>
<eesti> - ostetud, </eesti>
<inglise> under this scheme during the previous week; </inglise>
<eesti> - tapetud; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) shall establish a detailed report of the controls which they have taken under the measures referred to in Article 3 and shall communicate this to the Commission each month. </inglise>
<eesti> a. koostavad &uuml;ksikasjaliku aruande kontrollreididest, mis nad on korraldanud vastavalt artiklis 3 osutatud meetmetele, ja edastavad selle igal kuul komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to Article 9 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 (4), Commission experts, accompanied where appropriate by experts from the Member States, shall carry out, in collaboration with the competent authority of the Member State concerned, on-the-spot checks to verify compliance with all the provisions of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artikli 9 kohaldamist, korraldavad komisjoni eksperdid, keda vajaduse korral saadavad liikmesriikide eksperdid, koost&ouml;&ouml;s asjaomase liikmesriigi p&auml;deva asutusega kohapealseid kontrolle, et veenduda k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse k&otilde;igi s&auml;tete j&auml;rgimises. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> The measures taken under this Regulation shall be considered to be intervention measures within the meaning of Article 1 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 729/70. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt v&otilde;etud meetmeid peetakse sekkumismeetmeteks m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 2 m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub selle Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall be applicable from 11 April 1996. This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
